# Modus Color Usage in SolidJS + Vite

## 🎨 **Design System Color Architecture**

**CRITICAL**: This SolidJS + Vite application uses a **9-color design system** that maps Figma variables to Modus's color system, available as Tailwind classes.

**Color System**: 9 Modus colors mapped to design system variables in `src/index.css`

## ❌ **FORBIDDEN: Raw Modus CSS Variables**

### ❌ **Never Use Raw Modus Variables**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Raw Modus CSS variables
style={{ backgroundColor: "var(--modus-wc-color-base-page)" }}
style={{ color: "var(--modus-wc-color-base-content)" }}
style={{ borderColor: "var(--modus-wc-color-base-200)" }}

// ❌ WRONG: Direct Modus variable usage
class="bg-[var(--modus-wc-color-base-page)]"
class="text-[var(--modus-wc-color-base-content)]"
```

### ❌ **Never Use Hardcoded Colors**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Hardcoded hex/RGB values
style={{ backgroundColor: "#ffffff" }}
style={{ color: "#000000" }}
style={{ borderColor: "#e5e5e5" }}

// ❌ WRONG: Hardcoded colors in Tailwind
class="bg-[#ffffff]"
class="text-[#000000]"
```

### ❌ **Never Use Generic Tailwind Colors**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Generic Tailwind color classes
class = "bg-blue-500";
class = "text-red-400";
class = "border-green-300";
class = "bg-gray-100";
```

## ✅ **CORRECT: Design System Colors**

### ✅ **Use Design System Tailwind Classes**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Design system colors
class = "bg-background text-foreground";
class = "bg-card text-card-foreground";
class = "bg-primary text-primary-foreground";
class = "bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground";
class = "bg-muted text-muted-foreground";
class = "bg-accent text-accent-foreground";
class = "bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground";
class = "bg-warning text-warning-foreground";
class = "bg-success text-success-foreground";
```

